My highlight of 2022 is trying out Therapy and honestly it is pretty f*cking amazing!

(I picked these uglass pics to go with the emotion of these words below lol)

I realized that all of the emotions I neglected and packed away over the years, were making my load heavier and weighing down on my progress.

When my Grandpa passed in April, I was empty inside by Grief, but I still had to wear a smile and carry on. That was my lowest point and nobody else could see the downward spiral.

Especially being self-employed, I just had to carry on, when I wasn’t okay. I was actually burnt out with trying to run a business, being a BRAND and jumped ship into the corporate waters for relief. 

Lack of motivation, procrastination, imposter syndrome and pretty much everything that could block a creative from being creative had found it’s way into my life and in 2023 all that sh*t gotta go!! Leave TONIGHT!! 😂

Riddle back!

*This verbiage is the most personal I have ever gotten on Social Media and I know i’m rambling , but I hope it helps someone else going through it.

 — (thanks therapy)
